<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4287] Maven artifact file names do not match dist/ file names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4287</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the solr artifact, the war file name has the format &quot;solr-X.Y.Z.war&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://search.maven.org/#artifactdetails%7Corg.apache.solr%7Csolr%7C4.0.0%7Cwar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://search.maven.org/#artifactdetails%7Corg.apache.solr%7Csolr%7C4.0.0%7Cwar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when building from source or downloading the dist/ built war file, it is named &quot;apache-solr-X.Y.Z.war&quot;.  This should really be the same...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Preferably the &quot;apache-&quot; could just be removed, since the lucene build does not appear to use the same convention.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
